<a class="definition-word" data-category="cellular-biology" id="cell">Cell</a> - The fundamental structural unit of all life. The cell consists primarily of an outer <a href="#cell_membrane">plasma membrane</a>, which separates it from the environment; the genetic material (<a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a>), which encodes <a href="#heredity">heritable</a> information for the maintainance of life; and the cytoplasm, a heterogeneous assemblage of ions, molecules, and fluid.